------
best practices:

- use addCleanup instead of tearDown in test classes
- when POST methods create something, send back a 201 not a 200.
- make sure http DELETE is not used for batch delete.
- look for opportunities to use dictionary and set comprehensions.
- every page where we want to show list items in the sidebar has to have a tag state object passed to
  the template.  that's because the sidebar (base.html) requires both wordlist_id and a list_type
  in order to render list-specific menu items, and a tag state object has both.

  note that WITHOUT a tag state object, we will be fine, but we won't have any wordlist context to render.

- if a hidden field is not defined or is not passed in to the template, it must be wrapped with an {% if %} block
  or else it will be rendered unconditionally, defined or not.  this will cause badness.



